BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gwKFTRph1mzFdR2dPUMDi
SUMMARY:Ragamala Indian Classical Music and Arts Celebration
DTSTAMP:20260409T031204Z
DTSTART:20260419T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Ragamala Seattle for a family-friendly day of Indian music
	 and art activities at the Seattle Asian Art Museum. 11 am-noon Enjoy the 
	beats and rhythms of Indian classical music by participating in a drum cir
	cle led by Ravi Albright of the Seattle Tabla Institute. noon-1 pm Learn t
	o sing Hindustani vocal music in this beginner-friendly workshop led by te
	aching artists Suchitra Iyer and Anindita Das 2-4 pm Enjoy a concert and p
	erformance from celebrated Sitar player Pt. Kushal Das accompanied by Shri
	. Sandip Ghosh on Tabla. Pt. Kushal Das\, renowned Sitar and Surbahar arti
	st\, was born in a musical family in Kolkata. His father Sailen Das was a 
	disciple of Lakshman Bhattacharya and Pt. Ravi Shankar. His uncle Santanu 
	Das was a disciple of Pt. Ali Akbar Khan. He started his training under th
	e guidance of his father and uncle. Later he received training from Sanjoy
	 Bandopadhyay and from Ajoy Sinha Roy \\(a disciple of Pt. Allauddin Khan\
	\) and took vocal lessons from Pt. Manas Chakraborty and Pt. Ramkrishna Ba
	su. Pt. Das will be accompanied on the tabla by Sandip Ghosh\, who has bee
	n a disciple of Pt. Anindo Chatterjee for the last 18 years. Sandip has ac
	companied distinguished artists like Pt. Ajoy Chakrabarty\, Ud. Shahid Par
	vez\, Ud. Shujaat Khan\, Pt. Hari Prasad Chaurasia and Vid. Kaushiki Chakr
	abarty. He is also a solo artist\, collaborating with bands worldwide.\n\n
	https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ragamala-indian-classical-mu
	sic-and-arts-celebration/18529078/2026-04-19T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & 
	Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ragamala-indian-classical
	-music-and-arts-celebration/18529078/2026-04-19T00
LOCATION:Olympic Sculpture Park\, 2901 Western Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BT6oB8vI-nXZYNBCE2Mxl
SUMMARY:You've Had It In You All Along
DTSTAMP:20260409T031204Z
DTSTART:20260419T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Artists: Barbara Earl Thomas | Tariqa Waters | Cristina Martine
	z | Robert Wade | Maikoiyo Alley-Barnes | Nahom Ghirmay “\n\nYou’ve Had It
	 In You All Along” is an affirmation of our capability to weather any stor
	m. It serves as a vital reminder that the tools required to reach your des
	tination are already etched within your spirit. We already carry the brill
	iance and the beauty of what it takes—the confidence\, the strength\, the 
	security\, the poise\, and the knowledge to achieve our goals. The grit\, 
	the rigor\, the radical ideas\, and the voice required to transcend the wo
	rld around us are not external gifts to be acquired\; they are inherent po
	wers waiting for the moment of their activation. \n\nIn the process of ove
	rcoming—when the pathway forward is unclear and the effort feels endless—i
	t is easy to lose sight of our own internal compass. When we stand face-to
	-face with rejection\, heartbreak\, or the heavy weight of difficult seaso
	ns\, this exhibition serves as a sanctuary to remind us that we have alway
	s been more than enough\, exactly as we are. Breakthroughs happen in the s
	pace where we are gentle with ourselves\, allowing for the activation of a
	n inner wisdom and intuition that has been present since our first breath.
	\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/you-ve-had-it-in-you-all
	-along/18494682/2026-04-19T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/you-ve-had-it-in-you-all-
	along/18494682/2026-04-19T00
LOCATION:Avery Barnes Gallery\, 120 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
